==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adjutancy
<hw>Ad"ju*tan*cy</hw> <pr>(-t⟦ait⟧n*s⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[See <er>Adjutant</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The office of an
adjutant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Skillful arrangement in aid; assistance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It was, no doubt, disposed with all the <qex>adjutancy</qex> of
definition and division.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adjutant</ent>⟦br⟧
